d 'COEFCONV': module to compute comprehensive marginal effects from regression slope coefficients
d
d      coefconv computes 23+ marginal effect types for every
d predictor in the most recently estimated regression model.  It
d draws all    inputs from Stata's e() results (slopes, variable
d names, estimation sample) plus live descriptive statistics
d (summarize,	 _pctile, correlate) so no separate
d data-preparation step is needed.    coefconv is designed to run
d immediately after regress, ivregress, areg, or xtreg.  It will
d also run after non-linear    estimators but will warn that
d linear-slope marginal effects are approximations in those cases. 
d
d KW: regression
d KW: marginal efffects
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260517
d
d Author: Noman Arshed,   Sunway Business School, Sunway University
d Support: email nouman.arshed@@gmail.com
d
f coefconv.ado
f coefconv.sthlp
f coefconv_plot.ado
f coefconv_examples.do
f coefconv_manual.pdf
